in_2529144\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kbw1665702936111.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kbw1665702936111.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kbw1665702936111.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kbw1665702936111\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Configuring DB2 for Unicode\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Edit the application assignment file and database configuration files to configure the DB2 connector for Unicode.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__li_d24143e1_d24144e1_d24145e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To maximize Unicode capabilities:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__li_d24146e1_d24147e1_d24148e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Use a Unicode database\n (except for iSeries).\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__li_d24149e1_d24150e1_d24151e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the application assignment file, set <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF8</code>.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__li_d24152e1_d24153e1_d24154e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To enable limited Unicode support for a non-Unicode database:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__li_d24155e1_d24156e1_d24157e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To enable Unicode only in fields that use a W packing code, set <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span> to the code page used by the database.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__li_d24158e1_d24159e1_d24160e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To enable Unicode in fields that use either W or C packing codes, set <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF8</code>.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__li_d24161e1_d24162e1_d24163e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__p_d49670e1_d49671e1_d49672e1\">On Windows and Unix set the\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">alt_collate</code> configuration parameter using one of the\n                     following commands, then stop and restart the database for the parameter to\n                     take effect: </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">update db cfg using alt_collate identity_16bit \nupdate db cfg using alt_collate uca400_no\nupdate db cfg using alt_collate uca400_lth</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">alt_collate</code> makes it possible for Uniface to add\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">CCSID UNICODE</code> to the table definitions. Otherwise, using\n                        the W packing code or setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span> to\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF8</code> will result in the following error:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">SQL0622N The clause \"CCSID UNICODE\" is invalid for this database. SQLSTATE=56031</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"kbw1665702936111__li_d24164e1_d24165e1_d24166e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To disable Unicode completely, in the application assignment file, set the unicode connector option off:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">USYS$DB2_PARAMS unicode = off</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azs1665703222737.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$DEF_CHARSET</a><p>Specify the default character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zxs1665702727948.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>unicode</a><p>Enable or disable Unicode support.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bex1665702936034.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Support for Unicode in DB2 Connector</a><p>The Uniface DB2 connector enables Unicode support (with some limitations). By default, Unicode support is enabled.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529144\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529144\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring DB2 for Unicode Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configuring DB2 for Unicode Edit the application assignment file and database configuration files to configure the DB2 connector for Unicode. To maximize Unicode capabilities: Use a Unicode database (except for iSeries). In the application assignment file, set $DEF_CHARSET to UTF8 . To enable limited Unicode support for a non-Unicode database: To enable Unicode only in fields that use a W packing code, set $DEF_CHARSET to the code page used by the database. To enable Unicode in fields that use either W or C packing codes, set $DEF_CHARSET to UTF8 . On Windows and Unix set the alt_collate configuration parameter using one of the following commands, then stop and restart the database for the parameter to take effect: update db cfg using alt_collate identity_16bit update db cfg using alt_collate uca400_no update db cfg using alt_collate uca400_lth Copy The alt_collate makes it possible for Uniface to add CCSID UNICODE to the table definitions. Otherwise, using the W packing code or setting $DEF_CHARSET to UTF8 will result in the following error: SQL0622N The clause \"CCSID UNICODE\" is invalid for this database. SQLSTATE=56031 Copy To disable Unicode completely, in the application assignment file, set the unicode connector option off: USYS$DB2_PARAMS unicode = off Copy Related Links $DEF_CHARSET Specify the default character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code. unicode Enable or disable Unicode support. Support for Unicode in DB2 Connector The Uniface DB2 connector enables Unicode support (with some limitations). By default, Unicode support is enabled. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}